<problem><title/>
<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="h" from="1" to="5"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="k" from="-5" to="5"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="e" from="-1" to="1" exclude="0"/>
  <select name="a">
    <option><math>3</math></option>
    <option><math>2</math></option>
    <option selectWeight="2"><math>1</math></option>
  </select>

  <math name="factoredExpr" expand simplify="numberspreserveorder">$a(x - $e $h)^2 + $k</math>
  <math name="hAns">$e $h</math>
  <math name="b">-2 $a $e $h</math>
  <math name="c">$a($e$h)^2 + $k</math>
  <!--maths for incorrect answers-->
</setup>


<!--testing-->
<!-- <p>a = $a</p>
<p>h = $h</p>
<p>k = $k</p>
<p>e = $e</p>
<p>factoredExpr = $factoredExpr</p>
<p>factoredExpr{expand} = $factoredExpr{expand}</p>
<p>hAns = $hAns</p> -->

<!--testing-->

<p>Find the minimum value of the function 
  <me>f(x) = $factoredExpr.</me>
  <em>Note that the minimum value is a number.</em></p> 




<!--*********************************************
            Graphing Tool
**********************************************-->

<aside><title>Graphing tool</title>

  
<sideBySide margins="5%" widths="30% 70%">
<div><p>Graph parabola with given equation:</p> 
  <p><m>f(x) = </m> <mathInput name="eq1"/></p>

  <p>Graph a point at the proposed minimum value<footnote>How to find the coordinates of the vertex of a parabola from general form? Recall, there is a simple formula for the <m>x</m>, (or in this case, the <m>t</m>) value...</footnote>:</p> 
  <p><m>(x, f(x)) = </m></p>
  <p><m>\bigg( </m><mathInput name="userX"/> , <mathInput name="userMinGraph" bindValueTo="$userMin"/> <m>\bigg)</m></p>
</div>
  
<graph name="g1">
  <function name="givenParabola">$eq1</function>
  <point name="userVertex" fixed styleNumber="5">($userX, $userMinGraph)
    <label>$userVertex.coords</label>
  </point>
</graph>
  
</sideBySide>

<p>If your solution is correct the graphed point will occur at the minimum value of the graphed function.</p>

</aside>  

<!--*********************************************
            User solution input
**********************************************-->


  
<p><m>\text{min} = </m> 
  <answer name="ans9">
    <mathInput name="userMin"/>
    <award name="correct">
      <when>$userMin{isResponse} = $k</when>
    </award>

    <award name="usedH" credit="0">
      <when>$userMin{isResponse} = $hAns</when>
    </award>
  </answer>
</p>



